text.section:
A tax collector may not pay interest on a refund if the claim for refund is:
made under any provision other than § 13-901(a)(1) or (2) or (d)(1)(i) or (2) of this title;
based on:
an error or mistake of the claimant not attributable to the State or a unit of the State government;
withholding excess income tax;
an overpayment of estimated financial institution franchise tax or estimated income tax; or
an overpayment of Maryland estate tax based on an inheritance tax payment made after payment of Maryland estate tax; or
made for Maryland estate tax or Maryland generation-skipping transfer tax more than 1 year after the event on which the claim is based.
